Package surfaces

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Impervious
    Impervious is a subclass of Surface

    RoffCoef: For impervious this value is 1 since impervious absorbs nothing
    SType: This is the type of surface we are working with (10:alum_root, 11:asphalt_root, 20:asphalt_ground, 21:concrete_ground)
    SSHEAT: Specific heat of the given surface which will vary based on the type of surface
    SDepth: The depth of the surface we are working with which will vary based on the type of surface
    SMass: The mass of the specific surface which will vary based on the type of surface
    ArrayList: ArrayList of doubles to hold the simulation results
    TYPE: Interger value assigned to a surface which is used for the GUI
    Pervious
    Pervious is the subclass of Surface

    iflRate: Infiltration rate of the surface in inches per min
    RoffCoef: Runoff Coefficient which varies based upon the infiltration rate
    ArrayList: ArrayList of doubles to hold the simulation results
    TYPE: Interger value assigned to a surface which is used for the GUI
    DSSHEAT: Specific heat of dry soil in j/kg C
    SMASS: Mass of 1 cubic foot of dry soil expressed in kg
    Saturated
    Saturated is a subclass of Surface

    iflRate: Infiltration rate of the surface in inches per min
    RoffCoef: For saturated this value is .9 since saturated does not absorb much
    ArrayList: ArrayList of doubles to hold the simulation results
    WSSHEAT: The is the specific heat of wet soil expressed in j/kg C
    SMASS: Mass of 1 cubic foot of wet soil expressed in kg
    TYPE: Interger value assigned to a surface which is used for the GUI
    Surface
    Surface is the abstract base class

    evRate: evaporation rate in inches per minute
    wTblDpth: water table depth in feet
    length: length of a given surface in feet
    width: width of a given surface in feet
    sqFeet: calculated square footage of a given surface
    rnRate: rate of the storm in inches per hour
    strmDuration: duration of the storm in minutes
    srfcTemp: temperature of a given surface in Celcius
    rnTemp: temperature of the rain in Celcius
    ACRE: size of an acre in square feet
    GCFT: size of a gallon in cubic feet
    WSHEAT: specific heat of water in j/kg C
    WMASS: Mass of 1 gallon of water expressed in kg
